node.text:
Today we’re lucky to be joined by @thekiaramel from Drag Queen Story Hour Raleigh, to read two books that teach us about pride and identity: Our Rainbow from @littlebeebooks and @glaad, and My Rainbow by DeShanna and Trinity Neal (@trinitysmamabear), and @art_twink. 

Before COVID-19, many of @dqshraleigh’s events took place at the LGBT Center of Raleigh (@lgbtcenterofraleigh). As part of our partnership this month, we’re donating $10,000 to the Center — if you enjoy this story time, we hope you’ll consider donating too. You can find a link to the center by tapping the link in our bio and selecting yesterday’s rainbow mural image.

NOTE: To celebrate and enjoy this fun event, we will be leaving the comments section turned on, however, comments that do not respect others and stray from our community guidelines will be taken down. You can find our community guidelines in the FAQ section of our site.

node.text: As thousands of happy families already know, Nuggets are great for getting the push and pull of proprioceptive play. But with our factory operating slower than usual as we cautiously navigate Covid-19, we know not everyone who wants a Nugget has one just yet. Thankfully, @candokiddo has come to the rescue! On the newest episode of OT Nugget, Rachel talks about her kiddos' motor play area, and how to create your own — for any home, and any budget.

node.text: One of the best add-ons to encourage additional Nugget play is one of the cheapest things around — blue painter’s tape! This week for OT Nugget, Rachel from @candokiddo shows off four simple games that you can play at home with just a Nugget and a roll of blue painter’s tape. As always, try it on your own and share with us using the tag #OTNugget! Have fun!

node.text: Happy Holidays! ❄️ OK, you don’t REALLY have to order your holiday Nugget in July, but with an especially busy fall and winter ahead in the world of shopping and e-commerce, we do recommend buying sooner rather than later if a Nugget is on your wish list. You won’t be waiting long for it, either — thanks to our hard-working manufacturing team, we’ve brought our shipping timeline down to 3-4 weeks for the first time this year! Tap the link in our bio to learn more about our new shipping timeline and what logistical factors we’ll have our eyes on in the months to come.

node.text: Just using this beautiful fort photo to drop the news that starting today, all orders ship within a month of purchase! We’ve been hustlin’ 💨

node.accessibility_caption: Three children of different ages inside a Nugget-based tent, Nugget has black fabric with colorful dots all over.

node.text: Ever wandered over to the Nugget Shop and noticed the Classic, Limited Edition, and Special Edition category names? Ever wondered what the heck they mean?  From multi-year mainstays like Koala to one-and-done drops like the @juneandjanuary Confetti Dot (pictured, 2019), color categories are our way of bringing some organization to the Nugget universe 🪐 Tap the link in our bio to learn more about what they mean, how they came to be, and some fun facts about our color process!

node.accessibility_caption: Tweet on mustard-colored background reading: “We have had a Nugget since mid-quarantine and 2 is JUST NOW inconsolable bc she found the zipper and it’s not filled with chicken nuggets”

node.text: The secret’s out: Nuggets are not filled with nuggets. We sincerely apologize for the confusion and the ruffling of any feathers 🐔

node.accessibility_caption: Young child and dog sitting on sage green colored Nugget couch with green, navy, and rust-colored straight lines forming a mural in the background.

node.text: Hope you’re enjoying the dog days of summer 🐶 #BambooNugget

node.accessibility_caption: Studio photo of two navy-colored  Nugget pillows: left one is in a smooth microsuede, right one a more textured double-brushed microsuede. Arrow to left pillow says “2018-2021” and arrow to right pillow says “August 2021.”

node.text: Some big news just surfaced — Submarine is on its final voyage! That’s right: our much-loved, classic nautical navy is retiring. But come August, navy will be back, with a brand new name (which we can’t wait to share), in double-brushed microsuede! We’ve seen the interest in having more double-brushed options in the lineup, and we’re excited to give this mainstay a cozy new makeover. In the meantime, if you’ve had Submarine on your mission log for a long time, now’s the time to get it! For more info on this sea change in our deep blues, tap the link in our bio.

Cartoon of a submarine periscope popping out of the water in the foreground, with a warm gradient sunset in the background. Text reads: “Submarine is setting sail!”
